## Implementation receipt

Implemented on 2026-07-19 without staging because the message-event log worker shared this checkout.

- `MessageDeliveryMode` replaces producer-facing lane and urgency types.
- The routing table now owns `platform`, `delivery`, and `formatting`.
- Compatibility mapping is fixed: `low → digest`, `normal|omitted → memory`, `high|urgent|critical → alert`; source text is ignored and explicit kind wins.
- Implicit-kind sends emit one bounded `notify.compat_v2.implicit_kind` OTEL row with the exact replacement.
- The SDK preserves whether priority was explicit, but no longer derives `level` or `immediateTelegram` from it.
- Contract-v2 immediate routes bypass signal suppression.
- Contract-v2 batch routes return `digested` only when an injected durable queue succeeds. The live default reports the missing verified assembler and falls back to immediate delivery. No current consumer drains contract-v2 queue items, so the default does not pretend batching exists.
- Contract-v2 delivery receipts no longer admit `suppressed`.
- Non-contract signal suppression remains unchanged.

Verification at implementation time: 64 targeted tests passed; full message-contract tests passed (13); full gateway tests passed (187); message-contract, gateway, SDK, and CLI TypeScript checks passed; scoped Biome and Oxlint passed; focused reviewer returned `CLEAN` after the queue/journal duplicate-delivery guard was added.

## Start gate

Completed. The deployed button-native canary passed, `campaign-pulse/reaction` was retired in `cd87f9be`, and steering authorized this slice.

